Praetulerim scriptor delirus inersque videri, &a “ For my own part, I had rather be esteemed a foolish and dull writer, provided my own faults please me, or at least escape my notice, than be wise and a prey to continual vexation.” The poet means, that he would rather be a bad poet, if he could only imagine himself the con- trary,than a good one at the expense of so much toil and vexation.
